{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1204bc78-fd4a-4355-8f60-2a1b2df9a8ec","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 drops support for older frameworks.** Specifically:\n\n- **`net462`** — ❌ Not supported. MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework **4.7.2** (`net472`).\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported. MSTest v3 requires at minimum **.NET 6.0** (`net6.0`).\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET 5 is also below the minimum.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to update your target frameworks**, e.g.:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net472</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nAlso, MSTest v3 consolidates packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package, so you can replace both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` with:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"54e2b56c-e519-4439-a9ac-0f301a068e86","outputTokens":264,"requestId":"9819:336ED9:461B42:5BE2A1:69FFF28C"},"id":"6785555f-eb68-4492-bd4f-b1b7e713f36b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:50:58.827Z","parentId":"770609f8-1a37-4315-913d-d7129baad416"}
